+
+# Testing Minesweeper++
+
+## Build
+
+```bash
+cd /home/ubuntu/repos/MinesweeperPlusPlus
+./gradlew jar
+# Output: build/libs/minesweeper-plus-plus-1.2.0.jar
+```
+
+## Launch
+
+Requires an X display (`:0` on the VM):
+
+```bash
+DISPLAY=:0 java -jar build/libs/minesweeper-plus-plus-1.2.0.jar &
+```
+
+The app opens a Swing window with the game board, menu bar (Game, Difficulty, AI, Help), status bar (mine count, Reset, Auto-Play, timer).
+
+## Key Test Flows
+
+### 1. Basic Gameplay
+- **Left-click** on a square to guess (reveal). Exercises `Field.guess()`, `validateAlive()`, `validateSquare()`, `countNeighbors()`, `notifyListener()`.
+- Clicking a 0-mine square triggers cascade reveal via `sweepField()` → `setKnownAboutSquare()` → `forEachNeighbor()`.
+- Verify: revealed numbers (1-8) are consistent with neighboring mine count.
+
+### 2. Mark/Unmark
+- **Right-click** on an unrevealed square to toggle flag. Exercises `Field.mark()`/`unmark()`, `validateAlive()`, `validateSquare()`, `notifyListener()`.
+- Verify: mine count label decreases by 1 on mark, increases by 1 on unmark.
+
+### 3. AI Auto-Play
+- Click **Auto-Play** button. Exercises `LogicalAI.play()`, `forEachUnknownUnmarkedNeighbor()`, `countNeighbors()`, `forEachNeighbor()`.
+- A "Game Result" dialog appears: "We won! Yay!" or "We lost. Darn."
+- Beginner difficulty is most likely to win; Expert usually loses (expected).
+
+### 4. Reset
+- Click **Reset** button. Exercises `Field.resetField()` → `notifyListener()`.
+- Verify: all squares revert to unknown, mine count resets.
+
+### 5. Difficulty Change
+- **Difficulty** menu → Beginner (10x10, 10 mines), Intermediate, Expert (30x16, 99 mines), Custom, Coastal Defense System.
+- Verify: board resizes, mine count updates.
+
+## Tips
+
+- Expert mode has 99 mines on a 30×16 board — first click often hits a mine. Switch to Beginner for reliable manual testing.
+- AI Auto-Play on Beginner reliably wins and exercises all AI code paths.
+- Check terminal output (`get_output` on the background shell) for Java exceptions. Clean runs show exit code 0 with no output.
+- The app bundles .gif icon resources (j0.gif–j12.gif) for square states. These must be in the jar.
+- No CI is configured for this repo. Verification is via `./gradlew build` (compiles + runs any tests) and manual GUI testing.
+- The AI menu has help levels (0–3) that affect `applyAIHelp()` behavior after each guess/mark. Default is 0 (no help).
+
+## Devin Secrets Needed
+
+None — this is a local Swing app with no external dependencies or auth.
